<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[498,1516,1083,1191]" box="[498,612,1083,1110]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<heading bold="true" box="[498,612,1083,1110]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" reason="0">Diagnosis</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[498,1516,1083,1191]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName authority="Castello-Branco &amp; Collins &amp; Hajdu, 2020" authorityName="Castello-Branco &amp; Collins &amp; Hajdu" authorityYear="2020" box="[498,687,1124,1150]" class="Hexactinellida" family="Euplectellidae" genus="Bolosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lyssacinosida" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="perezi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[498,687,1124,1150]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Bolosoma perezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[695,787,1123,1150]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is the only 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ijima" authorityYear="1904" box="[927,1039,1124,1150]" class="Hexactinellida" family="Euplectellidae" genus="Bolosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lyssacinosida" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[927,1039,1124,1150]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Bolosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with discohexasters and codonhexasters microscleres.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[498,1542,1225,1333]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
EXTERNAL MORPHOLOGY. Sponge fragment, cushion-shaped and compressible, 162 mm in length × 78 mm in width × 16–27 mm in height; fragment apparently without a peduncle, color light gray in ethanol (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[945,960,1306,1332]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">fi</emphasis>
g. 6).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[498,1542,1368,1715]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
SKELETON AND SPICULES. A few long cemented diactins (40–80 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1322,1338,1369,1395]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">m</emphasis>
m diameter and over 900 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[611,627,1408,1434]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">m</emphasis>
m long), which we assume are fragments of a peduncle. Choanosomal diactins with rough ends and rudiments of tangential rays (1,275–3,125 × 5–8 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1452,1468,1448,1474]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">m</emphasis>
m). Dermal and atrial hexactins and rare atrial pentactins with rough ends and sometimes random spines along the ray (270‒830 × 5‒8 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1176,1192,1528,1554]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">m</emphasis>
m). Microscleres are ball-like discohexasters (70‒80 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[769,785,1568,1594]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">m</emphasis>
m diameter), its derivates (stauractins, 42–50 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1340,1356,1568,1594]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">m</emphasis>
m diameter), and codonhexasters (155–175 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[866,882,1608,1634]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">m</emphasis>
m diameter, primary rosettes 27–43 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1324,1340,1608,1634]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">m</emphasis>
m diameter). The last one with six primary rays and secondary rays in number of four; discs with nine teeth (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[577,593,1687,1713]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">fi</emphasis>
g. 7).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[498,1542,1749,1857]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
DISTRIBUTION AND ECOLOGY. Known only from its type locality in the Rio Grande Rise (Southwest Atlantic), 1,022–1,013 m depth. This is the 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1185,1200,1790,1816]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">fi</emphasis>
rst record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ijima" authorityYear="1904" box="[1347,1459,1790,1816]" class="Hexactinellida" family="Euplectellidae" genus="Bolosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lyssacinosida" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1347,1459,1790,1816]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Bolosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the entire Atlantic Ocean.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="12.[498,1542,233,341]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
ETYMOLOGY. The speci 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[801,816,234,260]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">fi</emphasis>
c epithet honors Prof. Dr. Angel Perez (UNIVALI, Brazil) for granting us access to Rio Grande Rise materials, and for our long-standing collaboration in the study of South Atlantic deep-sea ecosystems.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[498,1541,377,603]" box="[498,600,377,404]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<heading bold="true" box="[498,600,377,404]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="0">Remarks</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[498,1541,377,603]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ijima" authorityYear="1904" box="[498,605,417,443]" class="Hexactinellida" family="Euplectellidae" genus="Bolosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lyssacinosida" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[498,605,417,443]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Bolosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises eight species (see comparative 
<tableCitation box="[1065,1146,417,444]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="13.[208,263,452,474]" captionTargetBox="[199,1861,523,1836]" captionText="Table 1 Comparative data for habit, anatomy, spicules and occurrence for Bolosoma spp. Data for new species presently generated. Data for previously known species gathered from the literature. All morphometric data are in micrometers (µm). n.o., not observed." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF5766452E163E53A4F29BA3A8028EE0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" tableUuid="DF5766452E163E53A4F29BA3A8028EE0">Table 1</tableCitation>
), up to now recorded only from the Paci 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[545,560,456,482]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">fi</emphasis>
c Ocean. The new species presents a unique set of spicules, indicating its distinctiveness from the remaining species in the genus. None of its congeners present the combination of delicate codonhexasters and “ball-like” discohexasters, which confers 
<taxonomicName authority="Castello-Branco &amp; Collins &amp; Hajdu, 2020" authorityName="Castello-Branco &amp; Collins &amp; Hajdu" authorityYear="2020" box="[1310,1405,537,562]" class="Hexactinellida" family="Euplectellidae" genus="Bolosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lyssacinosida" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="perezi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1310,1405,537,562]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">B. perezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1414,1502,535,562]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
obvious status as a new species. This is the 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[991,1006,576,602]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">fi</emphasis>
rst record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ijima" authorityYear="1904" box="[1154,1261,576,602]" class="Hexactinellida" family="Euplectellidae" genus="Bolosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lyssacinosida" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1154,1261,576,602]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Bolosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the Atlantic Ocean.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
